parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the IMS bearing can cause engine failure, leading to a loss of vehicle control and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Brass flakes visible in the oil filter

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the coolant fittings can cause coolant leaks, leading to a loss of traction and potentially causing accidents. The coolant leak can also cause engine damage and overheating.
symptoms: Coolant leak from the rear of the vehicle
coolant light does not come on
coolant fluid on the rear tires
engine coolant blows all over the engine and onto the ground.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the side airbag to deploy in a side impact collision can increase the risk of serious injury or death to the occupants, particularly to the head and torso.
symptoms: Side airbag fails to deploy in a side impact collision
no airbag warning lights or notifications
occupants may experience severe injuries or fatalities in a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cloudy headlight lens can significantly reduce the visibility of the road, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions. This can lead to costly repairs, injuries, or even fatalities.
symptoms: difficulty seeing the road at night or in low-light conditions.
